00:28:57.390 --> 00:28:57.940
aren't we?

00:28:57.940 --> 00:28:58.740
JULIE: We are.

00:28:58.740 --> 00:29:00.610
And mommies are important.

00:29:00.610 --> 00:29:05.700
BD WONG: Really, I have to
say, I consider my mother way

00:29:05.700 --> 00:29:08.010
more than I should in
various everyday decisions,

00:29:08.010 --> 00:29:10.890
like buying underwear.

00:29:10.890 --> 00:29:17.160
I'm just so-- it's so deeply
ingrained to me to please her

00:29:17.160 --> 00:29:20.070
that I think about
her to a fault.

00:29:20.070 --> 00:29:24.100
And it's not necessarily
good for me sometimes,

00:29:24.100 --> 00:29:24.920
but I do do it.

00:29:24.920 --> 00:29:27.490
And there are really positive
side effects of that.

00:29:27.490 --> 00:29:32.290
And I must say that choosing
this play, to do it here,

00:29:32.290 --> 00:29:36.910
and to do it here now, and to
kind of drop everything as much

00:29:36.910 --> 00:29:39.970
as I could to do it, because the
time commitment that it takes

00:29:39.970 --> 00:29:42.520
to do a play is really intense.

00:29:42.520 --> 00:29:44.050
And that means being
away from home.

00:29:44.050 --> 00:29:46.700
And I have a teenage son
and all of that stuff.

00:29:46.700 --> 00:29:50.290
So choosing to do
so, to do a play out

00:29:50.290 --> 00:29:57.040
of town, was made infinitely
more seductive or satisfying

00:29:57.040 --> 00:30:02.830
because my mom's here, and
because my mom is inviting

00:30:02.830 --> 00:30:05.770
my whole family, my
whole, gigantic--

00:30:05.770 --> 00:30:09.130
her whole family, who mostly
are still in the Bay Area,

00:30:09.130 --> 00:30:12.020
to come to the
matinee this Sunday.

00:30:12.020 --> 00:30:15.550
And then to have this big
party upstairs in the theater,

00:30:15.550 --> 00:30:17.500
and do that kind of thing.

00:30:17.500 --> 00:30:20.170
Because she is like a--

00:30:20.170 --> 00:30:25.090
there isn't one
prototypical Chinese mom,

00:30:25.090 --> 00:30:27.070
but there are
maybe four or five.

00:30:27.070 --> 00:30:28.780
[LAUGHTER]

00:30:28.780 --> 00:30:29.370
JULIE: Yes.

00:30:29.370 --> 00:30:29.690
BD WONG: Right?

00:30:29.690 --> 00:30:30.220
JULIE: Yes.

00:30:30.220 --> 00:30:33.790
BD WONG: And my
mom is the one who

00:30:33.790 --> 00:30:39.230
will do anything not to brag
by using bragging words.

00:30:39.230 --> 00:30:42.200
[LAUGHTER]

00:30:42.200 --> 00:30:46.030
If you look closely, there is
a lot of bragging going on,

00:30:46.030 --> 00:30:48.350
but it's very classy
and it's very--

00:30:48.350 --> 00:30:50.170
she never says anything.

00:30:50.170 --> 00:30:54.290
She lets everyone else say nice
things, and then she says--

00:30:54.290 --> 00:30:56.180
she just nods or
something like that.

00:30:56.180 --> 00:30:58.110
You must be very proud.

00:30:58.110 --> 00:31:00.660
[LAUGHTER]

00:31:05.570 --> 00:31:09.320
So she is in that kind of--

00:31:09.320 --> 00:31:13.460
it's kind of passive aggressive,
like she doesn't want to--

00:31:13.460 --> 00:31:18.530
but it's wonderful to be the
beneficiary or the recipient

00:31:18.530 --> 00:31:22.310
or the inspiration for
her doing these things,

00:31:22.310 --> 00:31:25.580
inviting all of her family
and friends to this thing.

00:31:25.580 --> 00:31:29.420
And not pushing them to come see
it, but telling them when it is

00:31:29.420 --> 00:31:33.140
and hoping that they come
and then feeding them.

00:31:33.140 --> 00:31:34.060
JULIE: That's key.

00:31:34.060 --> 00:31:34.750
BD WONG: Yeah.

00:31:34.750 --> 00:31:35.500
JULIE: That's key.

00:31:35.500 --> 00:31:36.920
Food talks, yeah.

00:31:36.920 --> 00:31:42.290
BD WONG: And she's kind of
a mascot of the production,

00:31:42.290 --> 00:31:46.040
